<br>
But day to day, I rarely buy it. I admit once when my duoing partner Ayevee (my RL girlfriend) and I were really close to levelling, we decided to go to CoM early on Saturday, and I sought it out. We wanted to ding as fast as possible, so we would feel free to hang around with guildies and do whatever the rest of the day. Another time, I was the only cleric in a group trying to break the room in KC where the mob who drops the monk epic &quot;pipe&quot; spawns. We wiped, as I was OOM before we finished off all the mobs. So, yes, I got a punt to Nexus, bought a KEI and gated back to my party. We broke the camp, and continued on. Maybe we were doing something wrong, maybe I don't know how to play my class, or maybe it was that having monks and rangers as MA means a lot of mana goes to keeping them alive in a place like that. Or maybe all of the above.<br>
<br>
All I can say is I am glad not to be a KEI capable chanter, I would hate the pestering it must generate.<br>
<br>
Now to rezzes. If you can justify charging 100pp to cast a spell in a safe zone, in between clicking combine, how much should a clicky cleric charge to go to some brell-forsaken zone, risking life and limb to give a player back 96% of the experience they lost cause the screwed up, or are in some place they don't belong? Someone the other night in the 911 chanell said &quot;250pp for rezzes&quot;. I said that was robbery. some folks agreed with me, some with him.<br>
<br>
Me I play it this way: if I am not busy, and I can get there in relative safety, I click for free. If they donate anthing more than 25pp they get tmperance (LoY era baby-aego, costs a DoT). If they donate less or nothing, and I have the mana, they get Shield/Resolution and if I feel generous a jasper-symbol. They always get a Celestial/Remedy. Sometimes I even refuse the donation.<br>
<br>
The only time I have refused a rez request (except if I have been busy in a group -when I think it rude to make them all wait while I run off) was when our raid force wiped in SEB and we were running back, and just got to the TT zone. Someone starts spamming me &quot;rezz plz, I'll pay&quot;. My reply: &quot;sorry, raid wiped I gotta get back to Seb, get my stick and start clicking&quot;. &quot;Please rezz, please, I will pay..please&quot; Jeez.<br>
<br>
Maybe I should change my ways, a few pp in the bank would be nice, I really want to buy my GF a Nightmarewood compound bow for her birthday in 4 weeks. But then I think, I just finished buying my resist kit, that took a month, and cost at least 4k plat, so I should be able to afford the bow in a few weeks if I save my plat.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp.<br>
<br>
 <p>Fundin Stoutheart<br>
MADCOW</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hildie>Hildie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:green;'>Tavern Patron</span></span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(4/7/03 6:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3209.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I am sick of KEI! and what about rezzes?</span><hr size=1> I dunno how you clerics do it, either.  It's bad enough being in the same zone with people wanting buffs.  Having to travel and spend time zoning and running and risking death yourself would do me in.  I actually asked for a rez in my guild chat  last night, for the very first time.  I felt guilty and horrible and selfish...and as I died in CC, it was humiliating, too.  Fortunately for me, I got my rez and paid for it with hero sandwiches  (the bugger wouldn't take my plat).<br>
<br>
If I die outside of a group or raid (which doesn't happen often...I prefer the safety of groups) I /ooc in the zone I'm in for a rez...and I ALWAYS offer 100 to 200pp.  (200pp if the cleric's group has to help with dragging duties.  And I've noticed the rogue will normally take my money for the drag even if the cleric doesn't.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )  I hate being dependant on other players.  I've never asked for buffs after getting a rez, never even asked to be healed from rez.  I don't expect it...A rez is what I asked for, and that's all I'm offering to pay for.<br>
<br>
I know clerics are being nice when they don't accept money from me...sometimes they hit cancel and would rather I trade them KIE.  That's ok too.  But I would like to say that I wouldn't offer the money if I didn't want them to take it.  You have done me a huge favor, and taken time to do so.  Please allow me to show my respect for your time by accepting my plat.<br>
<br>
As far as the seeming contradiction of not wanting to cast KEI and then /oocing it...  I am taking pity on the people wanting it when there is no other chanter in the zone.  It is an opportunity for them to have their KEI, at a price I am willing to take the time and cast for.  In addition, it saves me time to hit one button instead of typing replies when I get tells.  One tell, I can hit my hotkey that says &quot;/r Yes.  100pp.  Pottery wheel.  No exceptions.&quot;  But when I get a couple tells in a row, that would mean I would have to type in all their names and then the sentence explaining my price.  MUCH faster just to hit all of them at once with an /ooc...and prevents new tells until the next person zones in wanting kei.<br>
<br>
